annotationA: I-kappaB kinase epsilon (IKKepsilon) is a serine-threonine kinase that targets the inhibitor of apoptosis Diap1 for degradation. It also negatively regulates protein kinase C and the dynein adaptor nuf. IKKepsilon roles include specification of bristle cells, bristle cell morphogenesis, oocyte polarity, and dendrite development
annotationB: Myd88 is an adaptor protein functioning downstream of Tl and upstream of tub in the Toll pathway, a signaling cascade which plays a key role in various developmental and immune processes, notably embryonic dorsoventral patterning and regulation of antimicrobial peptides
